Activity: A20 - Participate in a discussion with friends about a cybersecurity event

Objective
The goal of this activity was to discuss a real-world cybersecurity incident with peers to better understand its impact, causes, and prevention methods.

Method
I had an informal discussion with my friend about recent cybersecurity incidents, including data breaches and scams. We shared knowledge, opinions, and personal experiences realted to cybersecurity threats. I also guided parts of the discussion by explaining technical concepts and security practices.

Findings
The discussion covered the following key points:
1. Many users reuse passwords across multiple platforms, increasing the risk of account compromise during data breaches.
2. Phishing attacks are still one of the most common threats, with attackers using realistic emails and messages to trick users.
3. Large-scale incidents like telecom data breaches highlighted how personal information can be exposed due to poor security practices.
4. Some participants were unaware of basic protections such as two-factor authentication and password managers.

Security Principle
This activity relates to confidentiality, integrity, and availability. Understanding real-world incidents helps protect sensitive data (confidentiality), ensures systems are not tampered with (integrity), and promotes awareness to maintain system access (availability).

Evidence
Photos in evidence folder

Reflection
This activity helped me understand that many people are still unaware of basic cybersecurity practices. It reinforced the importance of spreading awareness and educating others about common threats and simple protective measures. Discussing real incidents also made cybersecurity feel more relevant and practical.
